cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of accurately estimating predictive confidence in deep neural networks, which is a common issue in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial noise, which falls under the category of computer security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the proposed confidence measure is based on density modelling approaches, which is a common technique in neural network research, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
